00:17:47.547 --> 00:17:49.632
Hey, Director Bak!

00:17:50.174 --> 00:17:51.426
You're a damn genius!

00:17:51.509 --> 00:17:52.677
-Right?
-Yes!

00:17:54.262 --> 00:17:55.805
This is it!

00:17:55.889 --> 00:17:56.890
Hey!

00:17:57.599 --> 00:18:00.727
If you do that,
you two will end up on the news.

00:18:00.810 --> 00:18:02.395
How will you deal with the aftermath?

00:18:02.478 --> 00:18:03.771
She's a reporter.

00:18:03.855 --> 00:18:06.024
If you mess with her, she'll destroy you!

00:18:07.275 --> 00:18:08.902
He's got a point there.

00:18:08.985 --> 00:18:11.529
Yes, he does.
I think I lost my mind for a second.

00:18:12.739 --> 00:18:14.449
It won't work, Mr. Lim.

00:18:14.532 --> 00:18:16.993
Then what are we supposed to do?

00:18:20.997 --> 00:18:22.790
Director Bak.

00:18:22.874 --> 00:18:24.667
What is it?

00:18:24.751 --> 00:18:26.836
At first glance,

00:18:26.920 --> 00:18:31.007
fame might appear to be a good thing,

00:18:31.090 --> 00:18:33.384
but once your face becomes known,

00:18:33.468 --> 00:18:35.511
your private life is over.

00:18:35.595 --> 00:18:37.513
You know what I mean, Director Bak.

00:18:37.597 --> 00:18:40.558
I can't enjoy a meal in peace
when I'm out.

00:18:40.642 --> 00:18:43.436
What does that have to do
with the production press release?

00:18:44.103 --> 00:18:45.730
I'm just saying

00:18:45.813 --> 00:18:49.192
that it's best to be rich
and not be famous.

00:18:49.275 --> 00:18:52.028
Stop beating around the bush
and just say it.

00:18:52.111 --> 00:18:54.072
You don't want him
to attend the press conference.

00:18:54.155 --> 00:18:56.574
No, that's not it.

00:18:56.658 --> 00:19:00.161
I'm just saying
that instead of being somewhat famous,

00:19:01.162 --> 00:19:03.081
keeping a mysterious image

00:19:04.624 --> 00:19:09.337
and remaining a veiled, genius director

00:19:10.922 --> 00:19:14.133
may be an option for you.

00:19:14.217 --> 00:19:16.010
Mr. Lim, you're so selfish.

00:19:16.094 --> 00:19:18.429
Are you trying to block my career
because of your love life?

00:19:18.513 --> 00:19:21.265
I don't want to be forced
to stay an unveiled director.

00:19:22.475 --> 00:19:24.811
Who said anything
about blocking your career?

00:19:24.894 --> 00:19:26.896
You got it all wrong.

00:19:28.356 --> 00:19:29.399
Wait.

00:19:31.317 --> 00:19:34.112
What if we don't hold
a production press conference at all?

00:19:34.904 --> 00:19:36.030
Huh?

00:19:36.114 --> 00:19:37.573
I pray that we don't.

00:19:38.741 --> 00:19:42.036
Why do we have to do it
in the first place?

00:19:42.120 --> 00:19:44.706
There's nothing wrong with not doing it.

00:20:11.399 --> 00:20:15.111
These flowers are called anemones.

00:20:15.194 --> 00:20:18.698
I heard they symbolize hopeless love.

00:20:20.742 --> 00:20:23.369
And they smell enchantingly sweet.

00:20:27.040 --> 00:20:28.166
Why am I here?

00:20:32.086 --> 00:20:33.004
What?

00:20:33.796 --> 00:20:35.631
What the heck was that dream?

00:20:35.715 --> 00:20:37.467
What was that about?

00:20:37.967 --> 00:20:38.926
That was so weird.

00:20:42.013 --> 00:20:43.806
Mr. Lim Hyeon-jun, do you like me?

00:20:45.933 --> 00:20:48.311
I'll take good care of Ms. Wi.

00:20:48.394 --> 00:20:50.104
Are you worried a rumor might break out?

00:20:51.439 --> 00:20:52.982
If a rumor spreads, then be it.

00:20:53.066 --> 00:20:55.026
Can't I even date at my age?

00:20:55.109 --> 00:20:57.945
And they smell enchantingly sweet.

00:21:03.910 --> 00:21:05.995
I'm late.

00:21:06.704 --> 00:21:09.499
Gosh, this is a pretty hearty lunch.

00:21:09.582 --> 00:21:11.793
There's chicken, rice, and salad.

00:21:11.876 --> 00:21:12.877
It's pretty well-rounded.

00:21:12.960 --> 00:21:14.003
This is good.

00:21:14.087 --> 00:21:17.048
Yes, I'll be a bit more careful.

00:21:17.131 --> 00:21:18.466
All right, goodbye.

00:21:21.344 --> 00:21:22.720
How much longer
do I have to put up with this?

00:21:22.804 --> 00:21:24.013
What is it?

00:21:24.097 --> 00:21:25.890
I wrote about the markup
on idol photo cards,

00:21:25.973 --> 00:21:27.683
and got told off
for ruining the idol singer's image.

00:21:27.767 --> 00:21:30.937
It's their gimmick
that ruined their public image, not me.

00:21:31.020 --> 00:21:32.563
At least the PR team says it nicely.

00:21:32.647 --> 00:21:34.649
I recently wrote an article about a drama

00:21:34.732 --> 00:21:36.776
and got tons of hateful messages
from the actors' fans,

00:21:36.859 --> 00:21:38.361
filled with nasty swear words.

00:21:38.444 --> 00:21:40.488
Getting cursed at is part of being
an entertainment reporter.

00:21:40.571 --> 00:21:42.281
Getting cursed at is one thing.

00:21:42.365 --> 00:21:45.159
But when I write about
a celebrity scandal or suicide,

00:21:45.743 --> 00:21:48.996
I'm shocked at how I write it up
like it's not a big deal.

00:21:49.872 --> 00:21:52.125
Well, if it's that difficult for you,

00:21:52.208 --> 00:21:54.335
you could move
to a different department or media outlet.

00:21:55.419 --> 00:21:56.671
Why stay here?

00:21:56.754 --> 00:21:59.590
I loved watching movies and dramas
since I was a kid.

00:21:59.674 --> 00:22:02.468
Enjoying good media content as a viewer

00:22:02.552 --> 00:22:06.430
isn't the same
as stepping into that world as a reporter.

00:22:06.514 --> 00:22:08.933
And it may seem like
we only write gossip pieces,

00:22:09.016 --> 00:22:10.935
but there are celebrities
who reach out to thank us.

00:22:11.686 --> 00:22:13.938
Gratitude like that
is what keeps us going.

00:22:14.522 --> 00:22:16.649
I could ask you the same question.

00:22:16.732 --> 00:22:18.317
I thought you'd leave at the first chance.

00:22:20.486 --> 00:22:21.320
Well, I…

00:22:25.783 --> 00:22:26.909
I'm not sure.

00:22:26.993 --> 00:22:28.244
What did you say?

00:22:28.327 --> 00:22:29.495
What I'm saying is,

00:22:30.163 --> 00:22:32.999
instead of sending Ms. Wi
to the Kang Pil-gu press conference,

00:22:33.082 --> 00:22:35.877
would you mind sending
a different reporter?

00:22:35.960 --> 00:22:38.629
You called me all this way
just to ask me that?

00:22:39.839 --> 00:22:42.341
Circumstances came up, you see.

00:22:42.425 --> 00:22:43.676
When you ask a favor,

00:22:44.177 --> 00:22:46.512
you should explain
the circumstances first.

00:22:46.596 --> 00:22:48.389
Why are you so uptight?

00:22:48.472 --> 00:22:49.640
Consider how serious things must be

00:22:49.724 --> 00:22:52.476
for me, Lim Hyeon-jun,
to ask you this favor in person.

00:22:52.560 --> 00:22:54.270
There's no need to get emotional.

00:22:54.854 --> 00:22:55.938
Just explain it

00:22:56.564 --> 00:22:58.357
so that it makes sense to me.

00:23:04.363 --> 00:23:06.532
Well, something happened.

00:23:06.616 --> 00:23:08.492
It's too complicated…

00:23:09.535 --> 00:23:10.953
It's too complicated to explain.

00:23:12.872 --> 00:23:14.582
The truth is…

00:23:14.665 --> 00:23:16.417
This seems good enough to submit.

00:23:16.500 --> 00:23:17.877
Nice. Thank you.

00:23:22.924 --> 00:23:25.593
I hear you're doing an amazing job
here at the entertainment desk.

00:23:25.676 --> 00:23:26.802
Word has gotten around.

00:23:28.221 --> 00:23:30.973
I'm pretty exceptional, after all.

00:23:31.057 --> 00:23:33.851
So what brings you here all of a sudden?

00:23:33.935 --> 00:23:37.480
You're not here to ask me
to return to the political desk,

00:23:38.064 --> 00:23:39.065
are you?

00:23:39.148 --> 00:23:40.233
Actually, you're right.

00:23:40.942 --> 00:23:42.944
Really?
I'm returning to the political desk?

00:23:43.027 --> 00:23:44.111
Yes.

00:23:44.195 --> 00:23:45.029
But first,

00:23:45.988 --> 00:23:49.116
you need to destroy
all the videos you have,

00:23:49.200 --> 00:23:50.159
as if they never existed.

00:23:51.244 --> 00:23:52.453
You did what?

00:23:52.536 --> 00:23:53.663
-Onion.
-Onion!

00:23:55.081 --> 00:23:56.165
-Onion.
-Onion!

00:23:57.333 --> 00:23:59.126
Oh, that Onion.

00:23:59.210 --> 00:24:00.044
Yes.

00:24:00.586 --> 00:24:03.881
So the secondhand selling app
you said you've used before…

00:24:03.965 --> 00:24:05.925
Yes, that's right.

00:24:06.008 --> 00:24:09.136
I sold a rice cooker to Ms. Wi.

00:24:09.220 --> 00:24:12.932
Then the reason why Ms. Wi
looked strangely excited that day--

00:24:13.015 --> 00:24:15.309
Yes. She came out to meet me,

00:24:15.810 --> 00:24:17.019
but I'm not the one she met.

00:24:17.103 --> 00:24:18.688
I had someone else go in my place.

00:24:27.947 --> 00:24:30.658
I can't believe you did that on Onion.

00:24:36.122 --> 00:24:36.956
Oh, gosh.

00:24:39.375 --> 00:24:40.376
Seriously?

00:24:48.175 --> 00:24:50.428
Mr. Lim, it's a shame
to hear about your predicament,

00:24:50.511 --> 00:24:51.554
but there's no way around it.

00:24:51.637 --> 00:24:54.598
Regardless of whether
Ms. Wi attends the press conference,

00:24:54.682 --> 00:24:56.267
she'll see the photos taken there.

00:24:56.350 --> 00:24:57.935
Then what am I supposed to do?

00:24:58.019 --> 00:25:00.563
You and I agreed to team up,

00:25:00.646 --> 00:25:03.649
so you should suggest a solution
in a crisis like this.

00:25:03.733 --> 00:25:06.110
Imagine if Ms. Wi finds out I lied to her.

00:25:06.193 --> 00:25:08.279
Knowing her personality,
she won't stand for it.

00:25:08.362 --> 00:25:09.905
She'll swear never to see me again.

00:25:12.408 --> 00:25:15.161
If you get caught
trying to cover up this situation,

00:25:15.244 --> 00:25:16.370
it'll make things worse.

00:25:18.205 --> 00:25:19.415
Just tell her the truth.

00:25:21.208 --> 00:25:23.669
Why are you saying things
that don't help at all?

00:25:23.753 --> 00:25:25.046
That's not a solution!

00:25:28.424 --> 00:25:29.383
I want to

00:25:30.509 --> 00:25:32.261
stay at Sports Eunseong a bit longer.

00:25:32.845 --> 00:25:34.680
You're turning down
the investigative journalism team?

00:25:35.264 --> 00:25:36.682
But why?

00:25:37.183 --> 00:25:39.226
Don't tell me
you're still pursuing that case.

00:25:40.561 --> 00:25:42.104
No, it's not that.

00:25:43.773 --> 00:25:47.610
The entertainment desk has grown on me,
and it's been rewarding.

00:25:47.693 --> 00:25:49.236
Rewarding? Listen, you punk.

00:25:49.320 --> 00:25:52.031
They make you write up
30 to 40 articles a day here.

00:25:53.574 --> 00:25:55.743
Well, sometimes I get a dose of reality.

00:25:57.870 --> 00:26:00.498
But even if it's an article
that'll be forgotten overnight,

00:26:02.083 --> 00:26:03.542
there are readers out there

00:26:04.919 --> 00:26:06.545
who still want it and enjoy it.

00:26:07.380 --> 00:26:10.091
More than that, I feel more at peace
than I did at the political desk.

00:26:10.883 --> 00:26:12.134
So I'll stick around a little longer.

00:26:12.843 --> 00:26:14.303
I appreciate the offer you made.

00:26:15.221 --> 00:26:16.180
I'm sorry, Chief.

00:26:28.651 --> 00:26:30.903
-Yes?
-Hello, sir. It's me.

00:26:31.404 --> 00:26:34.073
I don't think we can get Ms. Wi to return.

00:26:34.156 --> 00:26:35.950
Why? Did she refuse the offer?

00:26:36.867 --> 00:26:37.785
Yes, sir.

00:26:39.620 --> 00:26:40.830
My apologies, sir.

00:26:40.913 --> 00:26:42.748
I trust you'll take care of that reporter.

00:26:42.832 --> 00:26:44.667
Stop her from causing more trouble.

00:26:44.750 --> 00:26:46.627
Yes, sir. Goodbye.

00:26:49.797 --> 00:26:51.382
I'm going to lose my mind.

00:26:52.049 --> 00:26:54.260
What if I end up
taking the hit from all this?

00:26:54.343 --> 00:26:56.053
Wi Jeong-sin, that punk!

00:26:59.557 --> 00:27:02.184
These clothes aren't really my style.

00:27:03.936 --> 00:27:05.312
Let's check out that place.

00:27:05.396 --> 00:27:06.605
-That one?
-Yeah.

00:27:19.368 --> 00:27:20.369
PRICE: 1,860,000 WON

00:27:21.495 --> 00:27:22.329
One million eight hundred…

00:27:23.789 --> 00:27:25.875
Jeong-sin, it's way too expensive here.

00:27:25.958 --> 00:27:26.959
Let's go somewhere else.

00:27:27.042 --> 00:27:29.295
Hey, don't be a chicken
and just choose one.

00:27:29.962 --> 00:27:32.214
Look at the price of this
before telling me not to chicken out.

00:27:32.298 --> 00:27:35.509
Choose one while I'm offering.
This is a rare opportunity.

00:27:38.387 --> 00:27:39.388
Then can I get this?

00:27:40.514 --> 00:27:41.682
-This one?
-Yes.

00:27:42.725 --> 00:27:43.601
Let's take a look.

00:27:44.810 --> 00:27:47.396
-It looks nice.
-And it's the perfect size.

00:27:47.480 --> 00:27:48.522
I knew you wanted it.

00:27:54.195 --> 00:27:55.613
Do you offer a 12-month payment plan?

00:27:55.696 --> 00:27:56.864
Yes.

00:27:58.741 --> 00:27:59.700
Thanks for this.

00:28:02.745 --> 00:28:04.788
You probably spent
about a month's paycheck.

00:28:04.872 --> 00:28:05.915
Are you sure this is okay?

00:28:05.998 --> 00:28:07.708
Of course. That's why I got it for you.

00:28:08.834 --> 00:28:11.378
You always nag me whenever I spend money.

00:28:11.462 --> 00:28:12.505
Why splurge today?

00:28:13.172 --> 00:28:15.883
It's not like I didn't want to get you

00:28:15.966 --> 00:28:18.135
nice clothes and shoes
at a place like this.

00:28:18.219 --> 00:28:21.180
We have no parents or relatives
who would give us money.

00:28:21.263 --> 00:28:23.265
I don't want to ask anyone for help,

00:28:24.141 --> 00:28:25.976
so I just have to cut back a bit.

00:28:27.478 --> 00:28:28.479
Be good to me, you brat!

00:28:29.563 --> 00:28:30.397
Yes, ma'am.

00:28:32.566 --> 00:28:33.484
Here, have a drink.

00:28:39.281 --> 00:28:40.366
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

00:28:45.621 --> 00:28:47.331
It seems like only yesterday
that you were a kid.

00:28:47.873 --> 00:28:50.626
Now look at us, drinking together.
How touching.

00:28:50.709 --> 00:28:52.670
Jeez, stop being so dramatic.

00:28:53.212 --> 00:28:56.549
Hey, do you remember
how I was a high school senior

00:28:56.632 --> 00:28:58.133
when you started elementary school?

00:28:58.217 --> 00:28:59.802
You'll never imagine
how hectic it was for me.

00:28:59.885 --> 00:29:04.390
Yet I still got into Hankuk University.
Aren't you proud of your big sister?

00:29:04.473 --> 00:29:06.976
Wow, you never fail
to turn things into a brag about yourself.

00:29:08.143 --> 00:29:09.103
Oh, right.

00:29:09.186 --> 00:29:10.938
-The press conference is tomorrow, right?
-Yeah.

00:29:11.814 --> 00:29:12.982
Are you attending?

00:29:13.065 --> 00:29:14.358
No, I'm not part of that.

00:29:16.360 --> 00:29:17.820
I wonder when I'll get to attend.

00:29:17.903 --> 00:29:19.989
Learn from me and work hard.

00:29:20.072 --> 00:29:21.407
Your day will come then.

00:29:21.907 --> 00:29:22.741
Sure.

00:29:23.325 --> 00:29:26.579
By the way, is it over with that guy
you were flirting with?

00:29:27.204 --> 00:29:28.163
What are you talking about?

00:29:28.247 --> 00:29:32.376
Remember the bro at work
who handed you the gimbap?

00:29:32.876 --> 00:29:34.086
Why do you call every guy "bro"?

00:29:34.670 --> 00:29:37.047
He's the president of our company!

00:29:37.131 --> 00:29:38.132
The president?

00:29:38.966 --> 00:29:40.968
That young, handsome guy is the president?

00:29:41.051 --> 00:29:42.052
Holy cow.

00:29:43.470 --> 00:29:45.389
You must be lucky with guys.

00:29:45.472 --> 00:29:47.891
Jeong-sin, make things work this time.

00:29:47.975 --> 00:29:49.393
That bro is definitely into you.

00:29:49.476 --> 00:29:50.477
I'm positive.

00:29:51.478 --> 00:29:53.439
It's not like that. Just eat!

00:29:55.649 --> 00:29:57.234
Why do you always hit me?

00:29:59.695 --> 00:30:01.947
Doesn't that mean I have a chance?

00:30:02.031 --> 00:30:05.701
Forget about that guy already
and come to me.

00:30:06.452 --> 00:30:08.203
I'm right here in front of you.

00:30:08.287 --> 00:30:09.538
I've always been here for you.

00:30:11.457 --> 00:30:13.167
And I'm still waiting for you.

00:30:43.781 --> 00:30:45.532
Seeing that you asked me out for tea,

00:30:46.700 --> 00:30:48.202
I'm getting a bad feeling.

00:30:52.122 --> 00:30:54.291
I wanted to return
the umbrella you lent me.

00:31:05.844 --> 00:31:07.346
I used this as an excuse to see you,

00:31:08.138 --> 00:31:09.848
but I actually need to tell you something.

00:31:12.601 --> 00:31:14.561
Mr. Lee, I can't return your feelings.

00:31:23.195 --> 00:31:25.823
I expected as much on my way here.

00:31:27.658 --> 00:31:28.492
I'm sorry.

00:31:31.245 --> 00:31:33.747
I think you should take a moment…

00:31:35.040 --> 00:31:37.084
to think about how you really feel.

