Seriously, why isn't
another panic attack coming?

00:34:50.152 --> 00:34:51.486
That came out wrong.

00:34:51.570 --> 00:34:53.947
Seriously, why isn't Byeong-gi coming?

00:34:54.031 --> 00:34:55.324
What are we going to do?

00:34:55.407 --> 00:34:56.700
Hello.

00:34:56.783 --> 00:34:58.785
-Hey, Director Bak!
-Byeong-gi!

00:34:58.869 --> 00:35:00.621
Ms. Wi is here!

00:35:00.704 --> 00:35:01.788
What should we do?

00:35:01.872 --> 00:35:04.791
I'm dressed totally differently
from when I met Ms. Wi that day.

00:35:04.875 --> 00:35:05.918
Will that be enough?

00:35:06.001 --> 00:35:06.835
Yes!

00:35:06.919 --> 00:35:08.462
She didn't suspect anything
when I met her,

00:35:08.545 --> 00:35:09.838
which means she's not observant.

00:35:10.714 --> 00:35:12.799
-But…
-As if she'll fall for this.

00:35:12.883 --> 00:35:14.468
Director Bak, what's wrong?

00:35:14.551 --> 00:35:15.636
I'm okay.

00:35:16.178 --> 00:35:17.930
Mr. Lim, we have to get going now.

00:35:18.013 --> 00:35:19.598
I'm about to lose it.

00:35:19.681 --> 00:35:20.891
What are we going to do?

00:35:20.974 --> 00:35:23.060
What else can we do? Let's go.

00:35:23.143 --> 00:35:25.854
-Seriously, I can't deal with this!
-Oh, man.

00:35:31.735 --> 00:35:33.111
Hey, this is a great idea!

00:35:33.195 --> 00:35:34.029
Gosh.

00:35:35.447 --> 00:35:37.240
-Byeong-gi?
-Director Bak!

00:35:37.824 --> 00:35:38.909
He's breaking out in a cold sweat.

00:35:38.992 --> 00:35:41.286
Hey, what's wrong?

00:35:41.370 --> 00:35:42.663
-Where does it hurt?
-I can't…

00:35:42.746 --> 00:35:44.581
All right, it's time for the photocall.

00:35:44.665 --> 00:35:46.541
"They say you can't fix people."

00:35:46.625 --> 00:35:48.168
"But I do."

00:35:48.251 --> 00:35:51.588
No one delivers this line
better than the actor himself.

00:35:51.672 --> 00:35:54.466
First up is the star
of Good Detective Kang Pil-gu,

00:35:54.549 --> 00:35:56.259
actor Lim Hyeon-jun!

00:35:56.343 --> 00:35:57.469
Please come to the stage.

00:36:00.222 --> 00:36:01.056
Hello.

00:36:02.265 --> 00:36:04.893
-Please look over here!
-Over here!

00:36:04.977 --> 00:36:06.770
Thank you for coming.

00:36:07.688 --> 00:36:09.481
Wow, cameras are flashing everywhere.

00:36:09.564 --> 00:36:11.483
Mr. Lim, you look amazing today.

00:36:11.566 --> 00:36:13.819
Keep looking amazing,
and please look straight ahead.

00:36:16.196 --> 00:36:17.572
Now look to the left and right.

00:36:17.656 --> 00:36:21.034
Mr. Lim, can you lift up your hand more
and make a heart for us?

00:36:21.702 --> 00:36:22.536
Sure.

00:36:22.619 --> 00:36:23.620
Very nice.

00:36:23.704 --> 00:36:26.498
-Great!
-Look here, please!

00:36:26.581 --> 00:36:28.125
We'll see lots of great shots from today.

00:36:28.208 --> 00:36:30.502
-Over here, please!
-Please look over here!

00:36:30.585 --> 00:36:32.629
-Look this way!
-Now a heart with your right hand, please.

00:36:33.255 --> 00:36:35.215
-Please look here!
-Over here too!

00:36:35.298 --> 00:36:36.216
Very nice!

00:36:37.342 --> 00:36:40.262
Wow, he's the best at fan service.

00:36:40.345 --> 00:36:41.805
That was great. Thank you.

00:36:41.888 --> 00:36:43.974
Now, could you wait to the side
for a moment?

00:36:44.057 --> 00:36:46.476
We'll continue the photocall
with the beautiful Ms. Gwon Se-na,

00:36:46.560 --> 00:36:48.645
who has joined the cast for season five.

00:36:48.729 --> 00:36:50.230
Ms. Gwon Se-na, please come out.

00:36:53.775 --> 00:36:55.027
Please look over here!

00:36:55.986 --> 00:36:57.362
You look beautiful!

00:36:59.031 --> 00:37:01.658
Look at all these camera flashes!

00:37:02.242 --> 00:37:03.410
Please make a heart with your hands!

00:37:03.493 --> 00:37:05.871
-Make a heart, please!
-Look over here!

00:37:06.455 --> 00:37:07.789
Let's try some different poses, please.

00:37:07.873 --> 00:37:09.291
She has the most charming smile.

00:37:09.875 --> 00:37:11.585
Please direct your gaze at the cameras.

00:37:12.335 --> 00:37:14.796
She's making all sorts of hearts for us.

00:37:15.422 --> 00:37:16.840
This is it for individual photos.

00:37:16.923 --> 00:37:19.843
Next, we'll move on
to the joint photocall.

00:37:19.926 --> 00:37:20.927
Okay.

00:37:21.928 --> 00:37:24.681
Make sure you get a good shot. Zoom in.

00:37:24.765 --> 00:37:27.059
-Stand closer together, please!
-Closer together!

00:37:28.101 --> 00:37:31.104
You're standing a little too far apart.
Please move closer together.

00:37:31.188 --> 00:37:32.689
-Shall we?
-Yes, please.

00:37:35.901 --> 00:37:36.777
Look here, please!

00:37:40.030 --> 00:37:42.032
How about making a heart with your hands?

00:37:43.658 --> 00:37:45.660
Here's a heart.

00:37:45.744 --> 00:37:47.412
A heart!

00:37:48.163 --> 00:37:49.539
A heart.

00:37:51.500 --> 00:37:53.418
I think we'd like to see more fun hearts.

00:37:53.502 --> 00:37:55.045
It's a heart!

00:37:55.629 --> 00:37:57.130
A heart!

00:37:57.964 --> 00:37:59.007
-A heart!
-A heart.

00:38:00.217 --> 00:38:01.426
Here's a heart.

00:38:04.554 --> 00:38:06.515
"LIM HYEON-JUN,
A WARM SMILE BEHIND THE COLD EYES"

00:38:06.598 --> 00:38:07.933
I've never seen a heart like that.

00:38:08.600 --> 00:38:10.435
-Over here, please!
-To the right!

00:38:10.519 --> 00:38:12.771
"LIM HYEON-JUN REJECTS GWON SE-NA'S HEART
HEARTS ARE DIY"

00:38:12.854 --> 00:38:14.773
Thank you so much!

00:38:15.607 --> 00:38:18.401
Let me begin by asking the reporters
for their understanding.

00:38:18.485 --> 00:38:21.113
Director Bak Byeong-gi,
who was scheduled to attend today,

00:38:21.196 --> 00:38:24.282
was unfortunately unable to join us
due to health reasons.

00:38:24.366 --> 00:38:25.867
We appreciate your understanding.

00:38:26.409 --> 00:38:29.121
-He got severe indigestion.
-I see.

00:38:29.204 --> 00:38:30.997
Let's change the subject

00:38:31.081 --> 00:38:33.333
-and continue by interviewing the actors.
-Yes.

00:38:34.167 --> 00:38:35.627
I see a lot of reporters are here today.

00:38:35.710 --> 00:38:38.046
Please raise your hand
if you have a question,

00:38:38.130 --> 00:38:40.173
and the actors will answer it.

00:38:41.508 --> 00:38:43.301
Please pass the mic
to the one in the sky blue shirt.

00:38:44.052 --> 00:38:47.514
Ms. Gwon Se-na,
what can we look forward to

00:38:47.597 --> 00:38:49.766
in season five
of Good Detective Kang Pil-gu?

00:38:49.850 --> 00:38:51.893
Well, unlike Pil-gu,

00:38:51.977 --> 00:38:55.147
I-su relies on solid evidence
when conducting investigations,

00:38:55.230 --> 00:38:56.773
so they're always at odds.

00:38:57.357 --> 00:39:00.652
I think their teamwork and chemistry
when solving cases together

00:39:00.735 --> 00:39:02.070
is something to look forward to.

00:39:02.154 --> 00:39:04.489
We look forward to seeing that chemistry.

00:39:04.573 --> 00:39:06.199
What sets season five apart

00:39:06.283 --> 00:39:08.994
from the previous seasons of Kang Pil-gu?

00:39:10.954 --> 00:39:11.913
In this season,

00:39:11.997 --> 00:39:15.083
you'll witness Pil-gu's downfall
as a corrupt detective

00:39:15.167 --> 00:39:18.295
and the tormented human side
of Kang Pil-gu.

00:39:18.378 --> 00:39:22.048
Make sure to tune into the drama
to check out these parts.

00:39:22.132 --> 00:39:23.925
I have a question for Mr. Lim.

00:39:24.009 --> 00:39:25.510
I heard you opened

00:39:25.594 --> 00:39:29.014
the Kang Pil-gu 5 set
exclusively for Sports Eunseong.

00:39:29.598 --> 00:39:31.683
-Is this true?
-Is that true?

00:39:31.766 --> 00:39:34.311
Seriously? Why only Sports Eunseong?

00:39:34.394 --> 00:39:35.228
That's so unfair.

00:39:35.312 --> 00:39:36.354
We're reporters too.

00:39:37.689 --> 00:39:39.191
No, of course not.

00:39:39.983 --> 00:39:42.485
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

00:39:42.569 --> 00:39:46.740
What happened was
that we had planned to give

00:39:47.324 --> 00:39:52.787
each media outlet
individual access to our set.

00:39:52.871 --> 00:39:54.372
Right.

00:39:54.456 --> 00:39:57.542
-That's right.
-So we decided to draw straws.

00:39:58.877 --> 00:40:02.547
And Sports Eunseong
happened to be picked first.

00:40:02.631 --> 00:40:04.507
Man, Sports Eunseong is so lucky.

00:40:04.591 --> 00:40:07.177
We plan to invite every reporter on set

00:40:07.260 --> 00:40:09.596
before we finish shooting the drama,

00:40:09.679 --> 00:40:12.265
so we'd appreciate it
if you could wait a bit longer.

00:40:12.349 --> 00:40:14.434
So they were going to invite everyone.

00:40:14.893 --> 00:40:15.936
Yes.

00:40:16.019 --> 00:40:18.939
Yes, please be patient.
Meanwhile, we'll take more questions.

00:40:19.606 --> 00:40:20.607
The reporter in the back?

00:40:21.191 --> 00:40:23.818
I have a question
for both Mr. Lim and Ms. Gwon.

00:40:23.902 --> 00:40:27.322
Is there a romantic storyline
between you two in season five?

00:40:27.405 --> 00:40:28.740
-No, there isn't--
-Keep an eye out for it!

00:40:33.078 --> 00:40:35.288
I'm assuming
there's nothing in the beginning,

00:40:35.372 --> 00:40:36.790
but it develops later on?

00:40:38.041 --> 00:40:39.459
-No--
-Many viewers

00:40:39.542 --> 00:40:42.212
have been curious
about Kang Pil-gu's romantic side.

00:40:42.295 --> 00:40:46.967
The writer is working on a script
that will meet everyone's expectations,

00:40:47.050 --> 00:40:48.385
so you can look forward to it.

00:40:50.011 --> 00:40:53.765
Do we finally get to see Kang Pil-gu
in a relationship, then?

00:40:55.267 --> 00:40:56.518
Well…

00:40:58.395 --> 00:41:02.065
Yes, Reporter Wi Jeong-sin
from Sports Eunseong!

00:41:02.983 --> 00:41:04.067
-Me?
-Yes.

00:41:04.567 --> 00:41:07.112
You held your hand up like this.

00:41:09.114 --> 00:41:10.156
What's your question?

00:41:15.495 --> 00:41:16.454
Well,

00:41:17.205 --> 00:41:19.249
I'm less interested in
Kang Pil-gu's romantic storyline.

00:41:19.332 --> 00:41:22.877
Rather, I'd like to hear how you portrayed
both the righteous Kang Pil-gu

00:41:22.961 --> 00:41:26.131
and the corrupt detective Kang Pil-gu,
a character who is both good and evil.

00:41:26.214 --> 00:41:28.675
I would like to ask about
the effort it took to play that duality.

00:41:29.384 --> 00:41:30.218
Thank you.

00:41:31.720 --> 00:41:33.013
As I said before,

00:41:34.681 --> 00:41:37.225
you'll be able to witness

00:41:37.309 --> 00:41:39.561
the tormented human side of Kang Pil-gu.

00:41:58.038 --> 00:41:59.080
Hello?

00:41:59.164 --> 00:42:00.623
Hello, Ms. Wi Jeong-sin.

00:42:03.418 --> 00:42:04.753
Hello, Mr. Kim Dong-jun.

00:42:04.836 --> 00:42:06.379
How are you doing?

00:42:06.463 --> 00:42:07.839
I'm calling to give you an exclusive.

00:42:08.715 --> 00:42:09.758
An exclusive?

00:42:09.841 --> 00:42:11.718
I'm working on a new project.

00:42:11.801 --> 00:42:15.180
I said you'd be the first person
I'd contact, remember?

00:42:16.931 --> 00:42:19.309
So, this is you keeping your promise?

00:42:19.392 --> 00:42:20.518
Thank you so much.

00:42:20.602 --> 00:42:22.103
I look forward to the exclusive interview.

00:42:22.187 --> 00:42:24.773
Of course. I'm an expert at interviewing.

00:42:26.941 --> 00:42:28.193
Right.

00:42:28.276 --> 00:42:31.654
My manager will get in touch with you
about the time and location.

00:42:31.738 --> 00:42:33.907
Thank you. I'll be waiting, then.

00:42:33.990 --> 00:42:34.824
Goodbye.

00:42:42.415 --> 00:42:44.709
So we can't avoid the surge
in production costs,

00:42:44.793 --> 00:42:47.545
but a transparent revenue structure
could resolve this.

00:42:48.505 --> 00:42:49.506
Sounds good.

00:42:51.216 --> 00:42:52.967
Chief, the next agenda is…

00:42:53.051 --> 00:42:54.052
Just a moment.

00:42:57.889 --> 00:42:58.807
Yes, hello.

00:43:02.060 --> 00:43:03.061
Excuse me?

00:43:05.146 --> 00:43:06.481
How badly is he hurt?

00:43:08.400 --> 00:43:09.734
Which hospital?

00:43:10.485 --> 00:43:11.611
Yes.

00:43:41.015 --> 00:43:42.350
Damn it.

00:43:45.145 --> 00:43:46.438
Let's take my car.

00:43:48.022 --> 00:43:49.399
You can't drive in this state.

00:44:06.124 --> 00:44:07.041
What's your kid's name?

00:44:07.792 --> 00:44:08.668
Jae-ha.

00:44:10.378 --> 00:44:11.379
Yun Jae-ha.

00:44:13.590 --> 00:44:17.594
I think you should take a moment
to think about how you really feel.

00:44:18.136 --> 00:44:20.054
At the end of your gaze,

00:44:21.055 --> 00:44:23.391
it was always the chief.

00:44:41.034 --> 00:44:41.868
Yes?

00:44:43.453 --> 00:44:46.247
Goodness, Director Bak.

00:44:47.290 --> 00:44:50.335
You must've been under a lot of stress.

00:44:50.835 --> 00:44:53.379
What did the doctor say?

00:44:55.006 --> 00:44:56.966
It's just stomach cramps and exhaustion.

00:44:57.050 --> 00:44:59.010
I'm getting IV fluids
and taking the day off.

00:44:59.093 --> 00:45:02.180
-Oh, man.
-How'd the production press conference go?

00:45:02.263 --> 00:45:04.682
Yes, thanks to you…
No, that's not what I mean.

00:45:05.517 --> 00:45:07.143
It went well enough.

00:45:07.227 --> 00:45:09.729
-I guess it was thanks to me.
-Come on.

00:45:09.812 --> 00:45:12.148
Thanks to my timely collapse,

00:45:12.232 --> 00:45:13.942
you escaped a crisis.

00:45:14.025 --> 00:45:17.862
Come on, don't say that.
You're making me feel bad.

00:45:19.072 --> 00:45:19.906
Mr. Lim.

00:45:20.490 --> 00:45:22.200
Yes? What is it?

00:45:22.283 --> 00:45:24.369
I can't keep hiding like this.

00:45:29.290 --> 00:45:30.875
Yeah, I know.

00:45:32.710 --> 00:45:34.379
Today, we got lucky…

00:45:36.172 --> 00:45:38.424
I don't know
if "lucky" is even the right word.

00:45:38.508 --> 00:45:41.427
In any case,
we got through today because I collapsed.

00:45:41.511 --> 00:45:43.930
But there's no guarantee
we won't get caught later.

00:45:44.013 --> 00:45:45.848
My face could get on
the behind-the-scenes footage.

00:45:45.932 --> 00:45:47.517
I agree with you.

00:45:49.435 --> 00:45:52.063
I wasn't sure if I should tell you this,

00:45:52.146 --> 00:45:54.357
but I think it's best that you know.

00:45:54.440 --> 00:45:55.817
What is it?

00:45:57.735 --> 00:45:58.945
The truth is, Ms. Wi…

00:46:00.738 --> 00:46:01.739
Yes?

00:46:01.823 --> 00:46:04.200
I don't think she likes the real you.

00:46:04.284 --> 00:46:05.118
What?

00:46:06.786 --> 00:46:10.206
To tell you the truth,
she told me something the night I met her.

00:46:10.290 --> 00:46:11.958
The one I fell for

00:46:12.041 --> 00:46:14.294
was Detective Kang Pil-gu,
driven by justice,

00:46:15.003 --> 00:46:16.921
not the actor Lim Hyeon-jun.

00:46:22.135 --> 00:46:24.721
Not Lim Hyeon-jun, but Kang Pil-gu.

00:46:24.804 --> 00:46:27.849
She said she only likes Kang Pil-gu,

00:46:28.558 --> 00:46:29.976
the character I created.

00:46:31.394 --> 00:46:32.395
No…

00:46:34.731 --> 00:46:36.399
No, that's not possible.

00:46:38.610 --> 00:46:42.322
You've been under a lot of stress
because people see you and Kang Pil-gu

00:46:42.405 --> 00:46:44.073
as the same person.

00:46:44.824 --> 00:46:47.702
I think Ms. Wi was confused
for a moment too.

00:46:47.785 --> 00:46:49.954
She liked Kang Pil-gu as a fan,

00:46:50.038 --> 00:46:53.124
but she liked Melomaster
in a romantic way.

00:46:54.042 --> 00:46:55.752
That's what I think.

00:47:03.259 --> 00:47:04.093
Then what about me?

00:47:07.347 --> 00:47:08.681
She only liked Kang Pil-gu…

00:47:10.892 --> 00:47:12.852
and Melomaster from Onion?

00:47:14.604 --> 00:47:16.689
She never had feelings for Lim Hyeon-jun?

00:47:17.273 --> 00:47:19.692
It may be hard to accept,

00:47:20.610 --> 00:47:22.236
but that's how it seems.

00:48:06.572 --> 00:48:08.908
Do you like Lim Hyeon-jun?

00:48:08.991 --> 00:48:10.118
Yes, I do.

00:48:10.993 --> 00:48:12.412
It's the first time in my life.

00:48:12.495 --> 00:48:13.746
I've never liked someone…

00:48:15.581 --> 00:48:17.375
so unconditionally.

00:48:17.959 --> 00:48:19.585
He was really cool, of course.

00:48:20.169 --> 00:48:21.379
He's manly,

00:48:21.879 --> 00:48:23.381
yet still has that boyish charm.

00:48:24.090 --> 00:48:26.676
You can be old and still be cool.

00:48:27.218 --> 00:48:29.929
Everyone has their own kind of charm
that suits their age.

00:48:30.430 --> 00:48:33.182
I think Ms. Wi was confused
for a moment too.

00:48:33.683 --> 00:48:36.060
She liked Kang Pil-gu as a fan,

00:48:36.144 --> 00:48:40.148
but she liked Melomaster
in a romantic way.

00:48:40.648 --> 00:48:42.400
That's what I think.

00:48:46.112 --> 00:48:47.280
That's not true!

00:48:47.363 --> 00:48:49.240
Wi Jeong-sin definitely liked the real me!

00:48:49.323 --> 00:48:50.491
Without a doubt.

00:48:50.575 --> 00:48:52.910
It's ridiculous to cater to every tantrum

00:48:52.994 --> 00:48:54.454
of a middle-aged man acting like a diva!

00:48:54.537 --> 00:48:57.415
The second you think you're special,
that's when trouble starts.

00:48:57.498 --> 00:49:01.586
I can destroy you
with nothing more than my writing.

00:49:01.669 --> 00:49:02.837
I don't want…

00:49:03.921 --> 00:49:04.881
your apology.

00:49:05.715 --> 00:49:07.175
Was I wrong?

00:49:13.347 --> 00:49:14.807
I like someone else.

00:49:15.808 --> 00:49:17.477
And I'm still not over him.

00:49:21.272 --> 00:49:22.273
I don't know.

00:49:22.356 --> 00:49:23.691
-Hey, Su-ji.
-Yes?

00:49:23.775 --> 00:49:25.777
What is it that women want?

00:49:28.946 --> 00:49:30.239
It's so complicated.

00:49:30.323 --> 00:49:32.658
Sure. I'll play the song you requested.

00:49:32.742 --> 00:49:34.076
What are you saying?

00:49:40.249 --> 00:49:41.793
"NASTY MAN"

00:49:57.475 --> 00:50:00.102
YOU MADE ME CRY LIKE SAD MUSIC
AND LEFT ME FOR A FARAWAY PLACE

00:50:05.358 --> 00:50:07.401
The lyrics are just spot on.

00:50:08.986 --> 00:50:12.448
IS IT REGRET
THAT LEFT BRUISES ON MY HEART?

00:50:12.532 --> 00:50:15.868
YOU ONLY GAVE ME PAIN AND LEFT ME

00:50:15.952 --> 00:50:20.373
I GAVE YOU MY HEART, MY LOVE, MY ALL

00:50:20.456 --> 00:50:23.668
BUT NOW YOU'RE LEAVING, LIKE A STRANGER

00:50:24.335 --> 00:50:27.588
Take the pain of goodbye with you

00:50:27.672 --> 00:50:30.550
Oh

00:50:30.633 --> 00:50:33.219
You heartless one

00:50:45.273 --> 00:50:47.275
GET GREAT PRODUCTS
FOR GREAT VALUE WITH ONION

